<p>Wikimedia user Tarquin points out that the natural rhythm of spoken language can be used to teach polyrhythms.</p>
<p>Above: The phrase &#8220;cold cup of tea,&#8221; spoken naturally, approximates a rhythm of 2 against 3.</p>
<p>Below: The phrase &#8220;what atrocious weather&#8221; approximates 4 against 3.</p>
